taxon="Theorem"
number="2.1" />).
    Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\underline {\operatorname {Pic}}_{X/S}\to  S]]></fr:tex> is universally open at the points of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\underline {\operatorname {Pic}}_{X/S}^\sigma ]]></fr:tex>.
    If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\underline {\operatorname {Pic}}_{X/S}^0]]></fr:tex> is closed (for example, if the <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X_s]]></fr:tex> are geometrically normal, cf. <fr:ref
addr="fga3.vi-2-corollary-2.3"
href="fga3.vi-2-corollary-2.3.xml"
taxon="Corollary"
number="2.3" />), then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\underline {\operatorname {Pic}}_{X/S}^\sigma ]]></fr:tex> is itself universally open over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.
    Finally, in the case of equal characteristic, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\underline {\operatorname {Pic}}_{X/S}^\rho \to  S]]></fr:tex> is universally open.</fr:p>
  
    
